Final Project Structure

plm_nids/
├── config.yaml                    ← all paths, hyperparameters
├── data/
│   ├── pcap_tokenizer.py          ← L3/L4-only tokenizer (9 tok/pkt)
│   ├── cic_loader.py              ← CIC-IDS-2017 per-day PCAP parser
│   ├── pcap_dataset.py            ← variable-length PyTorch datasets
│   └── dataset.py / tokenizer.py  ← FlowMeter CSV mode (kept for comparison)
├── models/  rwkv.py + plm.py      ← RWKV-4 backbone + PLM
├── training/ trainer.py           ← Phase-1 / Phase-2 trainer
├── evaluation/ metrics.py         ← PR-AUC, ROC-AUC, F1, FPR@TPR95%
├── inference/ scorer.py           ← AnomalyScorer + FlowStateCache
└── scripts/
    ├── train.py                   ← training entry point
    ├── evaluate.py                ← evaluation entry point
    ├── visualize.py               ← all 9 paper figures
    └── run_pipeline.sh            ← one-command full pipeline
Step-by-Step Instructions
Step 1 — Install dependencies (once)

cd /Users/vivsharma/VK_AI_LEARN/plm_nids
pip install -r requirements.txt
Step 2 — Full pipeline (recommended first run)

bash scripts/run_pipeline.sh
First run parses all PCAPs (~10–30 min) and caches flows to outputs/flow_cache.pkl. Every subsequent run skips parsing.

Step 3 — Train individually if needed

# Phase 1 only (benign LM, ~20 epochs on Monday PCAP)
python scripts/train.py --config config.yaml --phase 1

# Phase 2 only (supervised, loads Phase-1 checkpoint automatically)
python scripts/train.py --config config.yaml --phase 2

# Force re-parse PCAPs
python scripts/train.py --config config.yaml --phase both --no-cache
Step 4 — Evaluate

# Unsupervised (Phase-1 model, perplexity-based)
python scripts/evaluate.py --config config.yaml \
    --checkpoint checkpoints/phase1_best.pt --mode perplexity

# Supervised (Phase-2 model, classifier)
python scripts/evaluate.py --config config.yaml \
    --checkpoint checkpoints/phase2_best.pt --mode supervised

# Combined
python scripts/evaluate.py --config config.yaml \
    --checkpoint checkpoints/phase2_best.pt --mode combined
Step 5 — Generate all paper figures

python scripts/visualize.py --config config.yaml --mode perplexity
python scripts/visualize.py --config config.yaml --mode supervised
Step 6 — TensorBoard (training curves)

tensorboard --logdir logs/ --port 6006
# open http://localhost:6006
